<paragraph blockId="5.[187,1401,415,514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1918" box="[189,386,415,441]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri">
<emphasis box="[189,386,415,441]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Quedius hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in Middle Asia, where it is known from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1252,1394,415,441]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, through 
<collectingCountry box="[286,416,451,477]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[470,606,452,478]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[749,863,451,477]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Salnitska M. &amp; Solodovnikov A." box="[876,1262,451,477]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" pagination="117 - 159" refId="ref8995" refString="Salnitska M. &amp; Solodovnikov A. 2018 a. Revision of the Quedius fauna of Middle Asia (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Staphylininae). Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 65 (2): 117 - 159." type="journal article" year="2018">Salnitska &amp; Solodovnikov 2018a</bibRefCitation>
). The newly examined material provides the first record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1918" box="[732,856,487,514]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Quedius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri">
<emphasis box="[732,856,487,514]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Q. hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[927,1093,487,513]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
